nerds:item_22 a prov:Entity ;
    nerds:critiqueIssues "The Rupee icon is thematically incoherent—a minaret is Islamic architecture, and the rupee is Indian currency, creating a jarring cultural mismatch,Title split between 'The Voice' and 'from the Minaret' fractures the poetic weight of the full title and misleads audiences,Color palette reads more tech-startup or wellness brand than drama—lacks emotional depth or tension,Minimalist approach with only a currency symbol fails to convey narrative stakes, character, or atmosphere,No visual connection to the film's Middle Eastern setting or romantic drama themes,Director credit missing from poster entirely" ;
    nerds:critiqueScore "0.35"^^xsd:float ;
    nerds:critiqueStrengths "Background and accent colors are technically harmonious as analogous cool tones,Minimalist aesthetic could work with appropriate iconography,Subtitle hierarchy attempts to preserve the full title" ;
    nerds:critiqueSummary "A well-intentioned but fundamentally misguided design. The Rupee icon betrays a lack of research into the source material and creates an offensive cultural disconnect. The palette lacks dramatic tension, and the fractured title dilutes the film's identity. This reads as a generic placeholder, not a poster for a romantic drama set in the Middle East." ;
    nerds:critiqueTick 14 ;
    nerds:heat nerds:Cold ;
    nerds:inputFingerprint "http://example.org/nerds/item_0|http://example.org/nerds/item_12|http://example.org/nerds/item_19|http://example.org/nerds/item_21|http://example.org/nerds/item_4" ;
    nerds:passes false ;
    nerds:posterImage "output/temp/temp_poster_tick14.png" ;
    nerds:structuredIssues "[{\"issue_type\": \"color_palette_weak\", \"severity\": \"high\", \"confidence\": 0.7, \"remediation\": \"switch_to\", \"target\": \"action\", \"nerd\": \"GenrePaletteNerd\"}, {\"issue_type\": \"imagery_missing\", \"severity\": \"high\", \"confidence\": 0.6, \"remediation\": \"add\", \"target\": \"hero+icon_composite\", \"nerd\": \"IconNerd\"}, {\"issue_type\": \"title_hierarchy_confusing\", \"severity\": \"medium\", \"confidence\": 0.5, \"remediation\": \"modify\", \"target\": \"title_structure\", \"nerd\": \"TitleParserNerd\"}]" ;
